<subSubSection id="C3186552FFDFE354FF73505EFADFFCF8" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBD36D9FFDFE354FF73505EFADFFCF8" blockId="17.[151,1436,1796,2039]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FF73505EFEF2FC11" bold="true" box="[151,274,1796,1822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFFDFE354FE88505EFE22FC11" box="[364,450,1796,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1322,1346]" captionTargetBox="[186,1402,181,1298]" captionTargetId="figure-23@22.[186,1402,181,1298]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 14. Meriola balcarce, male (MACN-Ar 33021). a, habitus, dorsal view; b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559197/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFFDFE354FE2A505EFE07FC10" box="[462,487,1796,1823]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1436,1460]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,273,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-55@23.[173,1413,273,1413]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Meriola balcarce, genitalia. a, Female epigyne, ventral view (MACN-Ar 33021); b, vulva, cleared, dorsal view. c, male, left palp, prolateral view (MACN-Ar 33021); d, same, ventral view; e, same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559199/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">15</figureCitation>
c–f) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFFDFE354FD0F505FFC81FC11" authority="González &amp; Grismado &amp; Ramírez, 2021" authorityName="González &amp; Grismado &amp; Ramírez" authorityYear="2021" box="[747,865,1796,1822]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avalosi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FD0F505FFC81FC11" box="[747,865,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. avalosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FC8C505EFC22FC11" bold="true" box="[872,962,1796,1822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24557B0FFDFE354FC8C505EFC22FC11" box="[872,962,1796,1822]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFFDFE354FC1C505FFB97FC11" box="[1016,1143,1796,1822]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fasciata">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FC1C505FFB97FC11" box="[1016,1143,1796,1822]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. fasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the elongate body, and by the opisthosoma with a chevron pattern and a dorsal posterior sclerotized area, but can be distinguished by the shorter, straight RTA, the slender embolus and conical distal bulb projection, and by the presence of a distal spine on the prolateral side of the femur II. Females (
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFFDFE354FD61502AFD3BFC85" box="[645,731,1904,1930]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-18@21.[173,1413,181,1907]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 13. Meriola balcarce Platnick &amp; Ewing. a, female habitus, dorsal view (MACN-Ar 33021); b, same, ventral view; c, same, lateral view; d, prosoma, dorsal view; e, same, ventral view; f, same, lateral view; g, habitus, anterior view. h, male habitus, anterior view (MACN-Ar 33021)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559195" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559195/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 13</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13392A5CFFDFE354FD03502AFCE1FC84" box="[743,769,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1436,1460]" captionTargetBox="[173,1413,273,1413]" captionTargetId="figure-55@23.[173,1413,273,1413]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 15. Meriola balcarce, genitalia. a, Female epigyne, ventral view (MACN-Ar 33021); b, vulva, cleared, dorsal view. c, male, left palp, prolateral view (MACN-Ar 33021); d, same, ventral view; e, same, retrolateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4559199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4559199/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">15</figureCitation>
a–b) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C024D5AFFDFE354FBED502BFB9FFC85" authority="González &amp; Grismado &amp; Ramírez, 2021" authorityName="González &amp; Grismado &amp; Ramírez" authorityYear="2021" box="[1033,1151,1904,1930]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachelidae" genus="Meriola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="avalosi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FBED502BFB9FFC85" box="[1033,1151,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. avalosi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B976EACBFFDFE354FB62502AFB3FFC85" bold="true" box="[1158,1247,1904,1930]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24557B0FFDFE354FB62502AFB3FFC85" box="[1158,1247,1904,1930]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the relatively elongated bodies, chevron pattern on the abdomen, the wide anterior epigynal hood and the internal genitalia, but differ by the narrower hood and the short copulatory ducts. Additionally, females differ by having dense ventral scopulae on the distal segments of the anterior legs, and a distinct preening comb on metatarsus III and IV.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
